The paper deals with the problem of face recognition using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and proposes a new layer called Parametric Sigmoid Norm (PSN) layer to improve the performance of CNN. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the PSN layer is designed to address the problem of hard examples, which indicates that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also conducts experiments on face recognition datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the PSN layer is a type of normalization layer, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
